social_posts.post_text: Good morning @amyscreativeside and #igquiltfest. I’m a day late on “Why do I quilt?” So many reasons. But a lot of it is the draw of this craft which has so much history. There’s a lot of personal family history for me and a lot of personal inspiration that comes from the quilters in my family. 1️⃣ On this page you see Louvinia Clarkson Cleckley who is my great grandmother, Anna Gibson Bond who is another great grandmother and Jane Arthur Bond who is my great great grandmother. And me. 2️⃣ Louvinia was born enslaved in 1858, about 100 years before I was born. On the second page is one of Louvinia’s Lone Stars and some of the quilts that have come through my sewing machine from her. I spent a few years working on star variations inspired by her work. 3️⃣ Anna was born in 1868 and made many quilts while having ten children and teaching school. Her quilt built in vertical columns inspired a few of my quilts. 4️⃣ And Jane was born enslaved in 1828 and was my great great grandmother. She made a number of quilts after the war that we have photographs of and one of which I have. Pictured are her pink Irish Chain and some square based quilts that I have made. We all quilt for so many reasons and those reasons change and evolve over time. But we’re all a part of that continuum of quilts reaching through the decades and centuries. #igquiltfest2023day5 #slbphilly #janearthurbond #louviniasquilts

Good afternoon @amyscreativeside and #igquiltfest !  This post number two for the day and the prompt is favorite quilted project that isn’t a quilt. I’m not sure it’s completely legit since it’s not strictly quilted, but it is patchwork!  I’ve been collaborating with my wonderful cousin @eisroughdraft with her fabric lines that she’s released with @freespiritfabrics  My previous post is about my foremothers but the fact is that I’ve been collaborating for the last year with an actual live Bond which is thrilling!  e is a book artist and in addition to making quilts with her fabrics, we’ve been making books with my patchwork designs in her fabrics!  It’s a great way to use those leftover blocks, a new way to combine fiber arts and, perhaps most important, a new opportunity to make something beautiful!  #glyphsfabric #rootfabric #ebond #slbphilly #igquiltfest2023day6

Hi there @amyscreativeside and #igquiltfest !  Today’s entry is lessons learned. I learn something every time I put a quilt together so it’s hard to choose but I’m going to choose this Lone Star quilt made by my great grandmother. A few years ago I decided to spend some time making quilts using this quilt as inspiration. I had already made a number of Lone Stars quilts but I wanted to work on some variations. So I essentially started to work in a series. I did big lone stars. Then I did a little inverting of the points and focusing them towards the center. Then I deconstructed the stars and rearranged the blades laterally across the quilt. Then I deconstructed the blades and spread the rows of diamonds across the quilt. And then I shortened the rows of diamonds and arranged them in a chain link pattern. I learned that there are endless variations to be made. But I think the most important thing I learned was that by narrowing my options by focusing on one form, I liberated my mind to see more of what was right in front of me. I’m not a person who does well with too many options anyway. I get overwhelmed and freeze up. But purposely narrowing my field of focus really opened things up for me. Sometimes you need fewer options in order to see how many options you really have. #lonestarvariations #slbphilly #igquiltfest2023day7

Good morning @amyscreativeside and #igquiltfest. Scraps are an inevitable byproduct of what we do. When the pandemic hit I was trying to figure out something people could do with what they had sitting around (scraps) on a pattern that was easy to print off at home. This was the solution. I sorted my scraps and started piecing. I’m still at it now. The latest version incorporates scraps as well as orphan quilt block bits and leftovers from other quilts. It’s still working for me. #igquiltfest2023day8 #scrappystringdiamonds #slbphilly

social_posts.post_text: I just finished a zoom meeting with @mariashellart and @cindygrisdelaquilts for our Mega Workshop this September at @madelineartschool. I’m so jazzed!  Five days, three joyous quilt piecers with distinct styles and a common goal which is to make this the most amazing five day quilt experience ever. The theme is Composing with Units and we will focus on building, blending and composing with pieced units. We’ll be talking about color, shape and repetition. Bring your creative spirit, your curiosity and your favorite fabrics (and units if you’ve got them) and have a blast with us!  Check it out at MadelineArtSchool.com. #mariashellart #cindygriseldaquilts #slbphilly #piecingperspectives #madelineislandschoolofthearts

Quiltfest at Greenville SC is next week!  I’m teaching three classes. Thursday is Pickle Dish Unplugged. Choose your favorite pattern or patterns to make your own best Pickle Dish!  There are some spots left. Come join in!  So much fun!! Sign up at Quiltfest.com. #pickledishunplugged #quiltfest #slbphilly

I love flying geese and I’ve spent a lot of time designing for them. I’ll be teaching Release the Geese at @quiltfest at Greenville S C on Friday. This is a fun class with paper pieced curved geese and quick pieced straight geese. With those two you can design your own unique quilt - circles, curves or straightaways, or any combination of the three. Come join us for a great day on Friday, April 21. Sign up at Quiltfest.com. #releasethegeese #quiltfest #slbphilly

Saturday in Greenville is New York Beauty!  We will paper piece several different types of arcs for your New York Beauty you’ll have options that you can swap out to come up with your own perfect combinations. I’ll provide the patterns and instructions. This a fun filled class and there are a few spots left. Hope to see you there!  Sign up at Quiltfest.com. #newyorkbeautyquilt #quiltfest #slbphilly
It was a great weekend in Greenville South Carolina with @quiltfest !  Thanks for a fabulous weekend!!

I got to do a little storytelling last night at a wonderful fundraiser for @sistersoutdoorquiltshow about this quilt and my great grandmother Louvinia Clarkson Cleckley. Louvinia was born in Orangeburg South Carolina in 1858. She was born enslaved and lived her whole life in the Jim Crow south. Among all the things she did and all she experienced, she made many beautiful quilts. One was a grandmother’s flower garden quilt in minty greens and white. I’ll never make a quilt with all those one inch hexes, but this is my hexie quilt to honor hers.  bell hooks wrote about race and class and feminism, and also about her grandmother and her quilting.  We still come back to ourselves through our quilts. #louviniasquilts #bellhooksquotes #quilthistory #quiltersaffair #sistersoutdoorquiltshow

A wonderful cap to a wonderful week. Today was #comingfullcirclequilt at #quiltersaffair  Again, a wonderful group of students full of creativity and enthusiasm. Thanks everyone for an amazing day and an amazing week!! #sistersoutdoorquiltshow #stitchinpost #comingfullcirclequilt #slbphilly

Landed in Philly at 7:20. Gate wasn’t ready so we sat on the tarmac until we got off at The gate around 8:30. Here’s how much luggage has arrived at baggage claim by 9:30. Good thing I’m still on Oregon time or it would be past my bedtime. **Finally got my luggage at about 2AM. All good!

Hi @americanair !  Hello @philadelphiaairport !  My flight from Phoenix landed at 7:20. We deplaned at gate A11 at 8:30. It’s almost midnight. We’re told there is no crew to unload our luggage. Yet, a flight from Miami deplaned a few minutes ago at gate A16 and has had their luggage unloaded and delivered to them at baggage claim. There are a bunch of folks still waiting here for our luggage. Surely this is solvable. Do you have any interest in solving this problem?  Edit:  suitcases appeared at 1:56 am. Whew!!
Home again and back to it!  Lots to do and not enough time to do it which means everything is normal. Happy Monday, everybody!  #slbphilly

Stitch Please podcast dropped this morning from a live session at QuiltCon in Atlanta. It was such a gift to be there to be there with family @eisroughdraft and @cmoorearte as well as @latifahsaafirstudios and of course @blackwomenstitch. We talked about collaboration in fabric design and quilt design and about ancestors and shared some quilts. Grab a listen 🎧 if you’re so inclined.

So here’s what’s been going on. Some of you know I’ve been a metastatic BC survivor since 2015. So now I’m on the chemo train in an effort to best a recurrence. I’m weathering treatments well and we’re hoping for good results. I’ll take all good wishes and compliments on my new hairstyle. I’ll politely pass on detailed medical discussions. I’m trying to work classes in around down times as best I can. I’ll be at Oaks today with @quiltfest  for lecture and trunk show at 1:30. And I’m planning on making @madelineartschool at the end of the month on my upswing. Looking forward to seeing you all when I can.  Love to all!❤️❤️
